<h3 class="govuk-heading-m">Finding your credentials</h3>

<ol class="govuk-list govuk-list--number govuk-list--spaced">
  <li>
    <strong>Open the CloudFormation console</strong>
    <p class="govuk-body">
      Go to <a href="https://us-east-1.console.aws.amazon.com/cloudformation/home?region=us-east-1#/stacks" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="govuk-link">CloudFormation console in us-east-1 (N. Virginia)<span class="govuk-visually-hidden"> (opens in new tab)</span></a>
    </p>
  </li>

  <li>
    <strong>Find your stack</strong>
    <p class="govuk-body">
      Look for a stack named <code>LocalGovDrupalStack</code>
    </p>
    <p class="govuk-body">
      The status should be <span class="govuk-tag govuk-tag--green">CREATE_COMPLETE</span>
    </p>
    <div class="govuk-warning-text govuk-!-margin-top-2">
      <span class="govuk-warning-text__icon" aria-hidden="true">!</span>
      <strong class="govuk-warning-text__text">
        <span class="govuk-visually-hidden">Warning</span>
        If the status shows CREATE_IN_PROGRESS, wait a few minutes for the deployment to complete
        before continuing. The stack takes approximately 15 minutes to deploy.
      </strong>
    </div>

    {# Screenshot: CloudFormation stacks list #}
    <figure class="ndx-screenshot govuk-!-margin-top-4 govuk-!-margin-bottom-2">
      <img src="/assets/images/walkthroughs/localgov-drupal/screenshots/cloudformation-stacks-list-desktop.png"
           alt="CloudFormation console showing the Stacks list with LocalGovDrupalStack and CREATE_COMPLETE status"
           class="ndx-screenshot__image">
      <figcaption class="ndx-screenshot__caption govuk-body-s">
        The CloudFormation Stacks list showing LocalGovDrupalStack with CREATE_COMPLETE status
      </figcaption>
    </figure>
  </li>

  <li>
    <strong>Go to the "Outputs" tab</strong>
    <p class="govuk-body">
      Click on your stack name, then select the "Outputs" tab
    </p>
  </li>

  <li>
    <strong>Copy these three values</strong>
    <div class="ndx-credentials-list">
      <p class="govuk-body">
        <strong>DrupalUrl:</strong> The URL to access your Drupal site<br>
        <code>https://[random-id].cloudfront.net</code>
      </p>
      <p class="govuk-body">
        <strong>AdminUsername:</strong> Usually <code>admin</code>
      </p>
      <p class="govuk-body">
        <strong>AdminPassword:</strong> Auto-generated secure password
      </p>
    </div>
  </li>
</ol>

